    \titre {1} {Netmagis: Introduction}

    Netmagis is a complete application, which allows a network
    administrator to:

    \liste {
	\item {manage \gras {IPv4} and \gras {IPv6} addresses;
	}
	\item {generate data for your \gras {DNS server} and
	    get \lien {BIND} {http://www.isc.org/products/BIND/}
	    zone files \gras {always up to date and consistant};
	}
	\item {\gras {delegate} DNS management to other network 
	    administrators or every non-specialist of DNS management;
	}
	\item {specify groups of users and very fine \gras {access
	    privileges} on address (even until every IPv4 or IPv6
	    address), on domains, etc;
	}
	\item {manage \gras {DHCP allocations} (both static or dynamic)
	    with \gras {profiles} to parametrize network boot;
	}
	\item {use your existing \gras {LDAP directory} to manage
	    accounts, or manage accounts with the Netmagis database;
	}
	\item {manage a \gras {large number} of networks, users
	    domains, DHCP profiles, etc.;
	}
	\item {visualize with \gras {automatically generated network
	    maps} your network topology (switched or routed);
	}
	\item {give \gras {access on these maps to users};
	}
	\item {\gras {assign VLAN} to equipment interfaces via
	    a simple Web interface (for Cisco, HP or Juniper
	    equipments);
	}
	\item {\gras {delegate VLAN assignment} to other network
	    administrators or every non-specialist of equipment
	    management;
	}
	\item {access to \gras {traffic graphs} that you have
	    specified on your equipments.
	}
    }

    Netmagis uses a database describing your networks, privileges that
    you give to groups of users, DHCP profiles that you want to assign
    to DHCP ranges or hosts, etc. Netmagis is de facto a true \gras
    {network information system}.

}

